<paragraph id="24A207F7BB57EDE1FA9F930781F5A631" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Type specimens studied.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C3B56364292F69231BBCABC93EA17500" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Holotype (male, MNHN): &quot;Quito, Equateur, Benoit, i.1932[h]&quot;; allotype (female, MNHN): &quot;Puembo, Equateur, Benoit, 20.ii.1931[h]&quot;.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBFA8B9DBF7EDD1B84AE86BB8A5B260B" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" type="further specimens studied">
<paragraph id="DECE8C8D008EB413520ABEA2CD671CC6" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Further specimens studied.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="979C3F2F895A30ABB8B173AC62522A8A" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="E418DEAB2FA6D8ACB9DAB90A9951168E" bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">ECUADOR:</emphasis>
&quot;Pichincha-Quito, 23.vi.1985, Gustavo 
<normalizedToken id="FF74D87BE09E96EE1A90DB3E5DE45257" originalValue="Morejón[p]”">Morejon[p]&quot;</normalizedToken>
(1 male, 1 female, MNCN); &quot;Pichincha, Alluriquin, 6.v.1948, F. Grazo leg.[h]&quot; (1 male, NMPC).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6982F524DDE46C3530BA39DD8ADCD8C1" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">No difference between both sexes were observed and also no variability in the colouration apparent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="28247E724E4E79A20C194E8231280382" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
Aedeagus (Figs 76, 77 in 
<bibRefCitation id="C281DE5CB5128FC2BE672E51D2589D6E" author="Cobos, A" journalOrPublisher="Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria)" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" pagination="103 - 165" refId="B19" refString="Cobos, A, 1956. Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria) 5: 103 - 165" title="Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb." volume="5" year="1956">Cobos 1956</bibRefCitation>
) very short, widely spindle-shaped, median lobe simply pointed apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49E3AF1DDF7BE93DEF1A85425F94D9BD" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">Length: 4.0-5.5 mm; width: 1.7-2.0 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
